[
    {
        "text": "This is Jim Jarmusch.",
        "start": 0.5,
        "duration": 0.94
    },
    {
        "text": "I’m the writer and director\nof “The Dead Don’t Die.”",
        "start": 1.44,
        "duration": 4.62
    },
    {
        "text": "This is a scene that takes\nplace in the Centerville",
        "start": 6.06,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "police station.",
        "start": 9.6,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s a three-cop\ntown, Centerville.",
        "start": 11.16,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "Bill Murray, the chief.",
        "start": 14.67,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Adam Driver and Chloë Sevigny\nplay the other two officers.",
        "start": 17.19,
        "duration": 6.18
    },
    {
        "text": "There are two parts\nto this scene.",
        "start": 23.37,
        "duration": 3.33
    },
    {
        "text": "The first is\nOfficer Peterson —",
        "start": 26.7,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "Adam Driver — explaining to\nChloë Sevigny’s character",
        "start": 29.31,
        "duration": 4.62
    },
    {
        "text": "that there is, in fact,\na zombie apocalypse.",
        "start": 33.93,
        "duration": 3.972
    },
    {
        "text": "“It's zombies.”",
        "start": 37.902,
        "duration": 0.583
    },
    {
        "text": "“What are you saying?”",
        "start": 42.308,
        "duration": 0.917
    },
    {
        "text": "“Well, it’s the undead.",
        "start": 43.225,
        "duration": 0.965
    },
    {
        "text": "They’ve been reanimated,\ncaused by the Earth",
        "start": 44.19,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "having been pulled\noff its axis,",
        "start": 46.95,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "caused by the polar fracking.”",
        "start": 49.17,
        "duration": 2.225
    },
    {
        "text": "And the second\npart of the scene",
        "start": 51.395,
        "duration": 1.405
    },
    {
        "text": "is dealing with one of the\nundead who comes to life,",
        "start": 52.8,
        "duration": 4.59
    },
    {
        "text": "played by Carol Kane.",
        "start": 57.39,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "Her name is Mallory O’Brien\nand was known as the town",
        "start": 59.28,
        "duration": 3.18
    },
    {
        "text": "drunk.",
        "start": 62.46,
        "duration": 1.959
    },
    {
        "text": "- [screams]",
        "start": 64.419,
        "duration": 1.481
    },
    {
        "text": "These undead in our\nfilm have a kind",
        "start": 65.9,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "of vestigial memory\nfor one thing",
        "start": 68.33,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "that they were\nsort of obsessed",
        "start": 70.97,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "with when they were alive.",
        "start": 72.98,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "And in this case,\nbeing the town drunk,",
        "start": 75.6,
        "duration": 2.84
    },
    {
        "text": "her obsession was chardonnay.",
        "start": 78.44,
        "duration": 2.902
    },
    {
        "text": "“Look out, kids.”",
        "start": 81.342,
        "duration": 1.498
    },
    {
        "text": "I’m not a big\nsplatter film guy,",
        "start": 82.84,
        "duration": 3.22
    },
    {
        "text": "so all the zombies in our film\nare dried up and dust inside.",
        "start": 86.06,
        "duration": 5.098
    },
    {
        "text": "“Chardonnay.”",
        "start": 91.158,
        "duration": 2.197
    },
    {
        "text": "“I got this, Cliff.”",
        "start": 93.355,
        "duration": 0.857
    },
    {
        "text": "The visual effect\nis quite stunning",
        "start": 94.212,
        "duration": 2.738
    },
    {
        "text": "and was done by a\nwonderful company, Chimney.",
        "start": 96.95,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "It was quite daunting.",
        "start": 100.23,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "We had to have a\nstand-in for Carol",
        "start": 102.03,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "Kane for the actual\nswinging of the machete.",
        "start": 104.12,
        "duration": 3.71
    },
    {
        "text": "The machete itself\nwas only a very short",
        "start": 107.83,
        "duration": 3.97
    },
    {
        "text": "blade so that it actually\ndidn’t touch the stunt",
        "start": 111.8,
        "duration": 3.78
    },
    {
        "text": "person.",
        "start": 115.58,
        "duration": 1.118
    },
    {
        "text": "“Chardonnay.”",
        "start": 116.698,
        "duration": 1.596
    },
    {
        "text": "- [screams]",
        "start": 118.294,
        "duration": 1.324
    },
    {
        "text": "[gunshot]",
        "start": 119.618,
        "duration": 0.868
    },
    {
        "text": "Bill Murray’s last shot to the\nsevered head was improvised.",
        "start": 121.025,
        "duration": 5.175
    },
    {
        "text": "In each of the other\ntakes, he didn’t do that.",
        "start": 126.2,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "But I found that very funny.",
        "start": 128.75,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "Chloë Sevigny,\nas an actor, she",
        "start": 131.33,
        "duration": 2.83
    },
    {
        "text": "is a real master\nof small reactions.",
        "start": 134.16,
        "duration": 3.41
    },
    {
        "text": "And she is our kind of\nscream queen in the film",
        "start": 137.57,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "because she screams\nmaybe six times",
        "start": 141.11,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "throughout the entire film.",
        "start": 143.24,
        "duration": 2.39
    }
]